# The @schoen scope (the aislop AI-slop gate, vendored as a devDependency) is
# served from the self-hosted Gitea npm registry, NOT public npm. This pins the
# fork build (mtschoen/aislop -> @schoen/aislop, adds C#/roslynator + newer
# rules) so CI runs the SAME aislop the maintainer runs locally. Read access is
# anonymous; no auth token is needed to install.
#
# Gitea uses a self-signed (mkcert) cert. npm trusts it via NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS
# pointed at the committed .gitea-ca.pem (the public mkcert root CA) -- set in
# CI and for local installs. NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS *appends* to Node's CA bundle,
# so transitive deps from public npm still verify normally (unlike `cafile`,
# which would replace the bundle, or `strict-ssl=false`, which disables checks).
@schoen:registry=https://gitea.llamabox.internal/api/packages/schoen/npm/
